text: Alsen is an unincorporated community in East Baton Rouge Parish, Louisiana, United States. The community is located less than west of Baker and southwest of Zachary and east of the Mississippi River. ==History== The community was founded in 1872 by an agency of the United States Department of War known as the Freedmen's Bureau designed to help freedmen in the aftermath of the American Civil War. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in East Baton Rouge Parish, Louisiana Category:Unincorporated communities in Louisiana
title: Alsen, Louisiana
